  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I recognize a fake solar panel?",
  "response": "Detecting a fake solar panel can be challenging, but several indicators can help you identify one:\n\n1. **Brand and Label**: Genuine solar panels typically have clear, permanent labels with the brand name, model number, and certifications. Check if the labels look tampered with or poorly printed. Verify the brand and model online to ensure they match.\n\n2. **Price**: If the price is significantly lower than similar products on the market, it may be a red flag. Fake panels might be sold at prices that seem too good to be true.\n\n3. **Certifications**: Look for industry-standard certifications like ISO, IEC, UL, and T\u00dcV. These certifications should be permanently marked on the panel. You can also verify these certifications on the certifying body's website.\n\n4. **Performance and Specifications**: Check the power output and efficiency specifications. Fake panels often have inflated numbers that don't match the actual performance. Ask for a datasheet and compare the figures.\n\n5. **Physical Inspection**: Inspect the build quality. Genuine panels have uniform and high-quality materials. Look for mismatched colors, poor soldering, uneven grids, or flimsy construction.\n\n6. **Weight and Size**: Compare the weight and dimensions with the manufacturer\u2019s specifications. Fake panels might be lighter due to inferior materials and construction.\n\n7. **Testing and Warranty**: Reputable manufacturers provide warranties and performance guarantees. Ask for details and verify the warranty with the manufacturer. Test the panel's output with a multimeter under sunlight to verify the claimed performance.\n\n8. **Vendor Reputation**: Purchase from trusted vendors or directly from manufacturers. Check reviews, ratings, and feedback from other buyers.\n\n9. **Backsheet and Glass Quality**: Examine the backsheet and glass quality. Authentic panels use high-quality, durable materials. Fake panels might use substandard materials that can degrade quickly.\n\n10. **Documentation**: Authentic solar panels come with complete documentation, including installation guides, warranty information, and certifications. Check for the authenticity of these documents.\n\nIf unsure, consider consulting a professional installer or technician to help verify the solar panel's authenticity.",
